  • Method Details

    • printDocuments

      public void printDocuments()
      Prints the documents of a student using 4 categories: New, Title, Date of release and Name of the attachment. Prints documents for all the courses separately. Uses the StudentPrinterConfiguration object to print a nice and structured grid to get a clear summary of the student's documents.

    • printDocuments

      public void printDocuments​(int x)
      Prints the documents of a student using 4 categories: New, Title, Date of release and Name of the attachment. Prints documents for all the courses separately. Uses the StudentPrinterConfiguration object to print a nice and structured grid to get a clear summary of the student's documents.
      Parameters:
      x - The number of documents to be printed

    • printAllDocuments

      public void printAllDocuments()
      Prints all of the documents of a student using 4 categories: New, Title, Date of release and Name of the attachment. Prints all of the documents in one table by date. Uses the StudentPrinterConfiguration object to print a nice and structured grid to get a clear summary of the student's documents.
